49
00:07:56,410 --> 00:08:01,088
<i>I confess to spreading the
rumour on orders from Goldstein

50
00:08:01,115 --> 00:08:05,693
<i>that the war is not really with Eurasia,
but with Eastasia.

51
00:08:06,023 --> 00:08:10,151
<i>And that for years, in fact
since the days of our glorious revolution,

52
00:08:10,277 --> 00:08:13,313
<i>I had no faith in our future.

53
00:08:13,447 --> 00:08:16,780
<i>I forged government announcements
and falsified figures

54
00:08:16,908 --> 00:08:21,071
<i>quoted for agricultural
and industrial production.

55
00:08:21,203 --> 00:08:26,790
<i>As a result of mental disturbance dating
from my experiences in the atomic wars,

56
00:08:26,917 --> 00:08:30,748
<i>I was a willing subject
of Goldstein's influence.

57
00:08:30,879 --> 00:08:33,452
<i>I was stubborn and egocentric.

58
00:08:33,589 --> 00:08:37,088
<i>When own life thoughts
occurred to me, I revelled in them.

59
00:08:37,218 --> 00:08:41,713
<i>I went into the proletarian
zones. I had sex with prostitutes.

60
00:08:41,847 --> 00:08:45,050
<i>I deliberately contracted syphilis.

61
00:08:45,183 --> 00:08:49,180
<i>It was at this time
that I made contact with the Resistance.

62
00:08:49,312 --> 00:08:53,890
<i>I was personally contacted
by the arch-traitor Goldstein

63
00:08:53,915 --> 00:08:56,669
<i>and ordered to assassinate
Inner Party officials.

64
00:08:56,694 --> 00:08:59,150
- Bugger!
- <i>This I did.

65
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:04,544
<i>My agents forged documents and gained
entry to the Ministry of Truth...

66
00:09:04,794 --> 00:09:08,079
Thought crime is death.

67
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:11,660
Thought crime does not entail death.

68
00:09:11,756 --> 00:09:14,211
Thought crime is death.

69
00:09:15,677 --> 00:09:19,923
I have committed,
even before setting pen to paper,

70
00:09:20,212 --> 00:09:25,032
the essential crime that contains
all others in itself.

71
00:09:25,638 --> 00:09:30,715
... <i>encouraging my agents to deface
party posters and announcements.

72
00:09:31,432 --> 00:09:35,299
<i>I read and memorised Goldstein's book.

73
00:09:35,436 --> 00:09:39,932
<i>For 30 years, I have plotted
to bring down the Party.</i>

74
00:09:40,065 --> 00:09:42,057
<i>I was sick in mind and body.</i>

75
00:09:42,192 --> 00:09:46,567
<i>Together with my colleagues,
Aaronson and Rutherford,</i>

76
00:09:46,633 --> 00:09:50,796
<i>I did counterfeit
important Party documents,</i>

77
00:09:51,218 --> 00:09:55,062
<i>including ex-London permits
and travel passes.</i>

78
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:57,935
<i>And that by use of these documents</i>

79
00:09:58,623 --> 00:10:01,707
<i>my agents travelled freely
throughout Airstrip One,</i>

80
00:10:01,834 --> 00:10:05,203
<i>encouraging insurrection
and organising a huge counter plot</i>

81
00:10:05,338 --> 00:10:10,241
<i>to destroy the innermost faction
of the Oceanian leadership.</i>

82
00:10:10,576 --> 00:10:16,806
<i>Furthermore, I used my position
of privilege within the Inner Party</i>

83
00:10:18,432 --> 00:10:22,909
<i>to pervert and betray the truth at all
times and to suggest, wherever possible,</i>

84
00:10:22,996 --> 00:10:28,449
<i>that our traditional allies in Eastasia
were, in fact, our deadly enemies...</i>

85
00:10:29,123 --> 00:10:32,787
April 4th 1984.

86
00:10:34,931 --> 00:10:36,923
I think.

87
00:10:42,251 --> 00:10:45,915
To the past, or to the future,

88
00:10:47,664 --> 00:10:50,201
to an age when thought is free.

89
00:10:51,550 --> 00:10:54,337
From the age of Big Brother,

90
00:10:54,532 --> 00:10:57,699
from the age of the Thought Police...

91
00:10:59,034 --> 00:11:02,153
from a dead man,

92
00:11:02,732 --> 00:11:04,973
greetings.

93
00:11:37,951 --> 00:11:40,951
(SOUND OF ALARM FROM TELESCREEN)

94
00:11:52,527 --> 00:11:57,188
TELESCREEN: 30-40 group,
take your places, please.

95
00:11:57,244 --> 00:12:00,577
TELESCREEN: Right let's see which
one of us can touch his toes.

96
00:12:00,602 --> 00:12:04,053
TELESCREEN: Right over from the
hips, brothers and sisters please.

97
00:12:04,308 --> 00:12:06,763
TELESCREEN: One, two.

98
00:12:06,955 --> 00:12:09,576
TELESCREEN: One, two.

99
00:12:09,724 --> 00:12:12,215
TELESCREEN: One, two.

100
00:12:12,359 --> 00:12:15,443
TELESCREEN: One, two.

101
00:12:16,154 --> 00:12:20,615
TELESCREEN: Smith! 6079 Smith W.

102
00:12:21,039 --> 00:12:23,411
TELESCREEN: Yes you. Bend lower.

103
00:12:24,868 --> 00:12:27,359
TELESCREEN: You're not
trying, watch me.

104
00:12:35,941 --> 00:12:38,693
TELESCREEN: There, brother,
that's what I want.

105
00:12:38,968 --> 00:12:42,799
TELESCREEN: Anyone under 45
is perfectly capable of touching his toes.

106
00:12:42,860 --> 00:12:45,564
TELESCREEN: I'm 39 and
I've had four children.

107
00:12:45,589 --> 00:12:48,723
TELESCREEN: We don't all have the
privilege of fighting in the front line.

108
00:12:48,748 --> 00:12:51,155
TELESCREEN: Remember our
boys on the Malabar front.

109
00:12:51,370 --> 00:12:54,738
TELESCREEN: Just think what
they have to put up with.

110
00:13:11,532 --> 00:13:13,987
- Morning Smith.
- Parsons.

111
00:13:16,298 --> 00:13:19,632
- Heard the rumour?
- No. Good news is it?

112
00:13:19,657 --> 00:13:21,530
I should say so yes.

113
00:13:21,947 --> 00:13:24,153
Choco rations going up.

114
00:13:24,178 --> 00:13:27,594
- Really?
- 25g next week.

115
00:13:28,131 --> 00:13:30,170
Double plus good, eh?

116
00:13:36,367 --> 00:13:40,743
By the way Smith, I seem to have run
out of razor blades for some reason.

117
00:13:40,768 --> 00:13:43,305
Er you wouldn't happen to
have any spare would you?

118
00:13:43,430 --> 00:13:46,798
I'm sorry brother, I'm on the last one.

119
00:13:48,689 --> 00:13:54,143
<i>In 1983 Oceania's coal
output reached 630 million tons.</i>

120
00:13:55,333 --> 00:14:00,576
<i>In 1976,
coal output was 605 million tons,</i>

121
00:14:00,713 --> 00:14:03,879
<i>an increase of 4. 1 per cent.</i>

122
00:14:03,904 --> 00:14:09,457
<i>5.3 million tractors were produced,
an increase of 17.6 per cent.</i>

123
00:14:11,939 --> 00:14:14,725
I wanted to ask you if
you've got any razor blades.

124
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:20,253
I've tried all over the place. I've been
using the same one for six weeks.

125
00:14:24,913 --> 00:14:27,285
Did you see the prisoners
hanged yesterday?

126
00:14:27,310 --> 00:14:31,639
No I was working.
But I shall see it on the screens.

127
00:14:40,887 --> 00:14:43,556
We'll pick up a gin on the way.

128
00:14:45,883 --> 00:14:47,923
I'll have two.

129
00:15:02,685 --> 00:15:04,162
Give me a gin.

130
00:15:04,187 --> 00:15:09,540
<i>2 million .5 Victory recoil
operated heavy machine guns,</i>

131
00:15:09,945 --> 00:15:15,164
<i>6 million rifle grenades, 9
million Perry pineapple pin grenades</i>

132
00:15:15,884 --> 00:15:18,422
<i>and 1.4 million lightweight</i>

133
00:15:18,780 --> 00:15:23,073
<i>spigot-launching
antitank rocket projectors.</i>

134
00:15:23,412 --> 00:15:25,451
<i>Food production is also up...</i>

135
00:15:25,580 --> 00:15:30,123
- How's the New speak Committee?
- Working overtime.

136
00:15:31,282 --> 00:15:35,114
The plus big wastage is in adjectives.

137
00:15:35,487 --> 00:15:40,842
Plus big problem is timing the
language to scientific advance.

138
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:43,066
Yes.

139
00:15:43,682 --> 00:15:47,710
It's a beautiful thing,
the destruction of words.

140
00:15:49,435 --> 00:15:53,266
You won't have seen the
dictionary tenth edition yet Smith.

141
00:15:53,396 --> 00:15:55,603
It's that thick.

142
00:15:55,732 --> 00:15:58,567
The 11th edition will be that thick.

143
00:16:00,399 --> 00:16:04,017
So the revolution will be complete
when the language is perfect?

144
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:10,743
The secret is to move from translation
to direct thought to automatic response.

145
00:16:10,953 --> 00:16:15,614
- Language coming from here not here.
- Excuse me for intruding.

146
00:16:15,639 --> 00:16:19,506
We shall be rid of Goldsteinism
when the language has been cleaned.

147
00:16:19,635 --> 00:16:22,061
I couldn't be more in agreement
with you brother.

148
00:16:22,086 --> 00:16:23,378
Absolutely

149
00:16:27,258 --> 00:16:31,171
<i>Praise be to our leader
and the Party workers.</i>

150
00:16:34,813 --> 00:16:38,395
<i>Other munitions production figures
are as follows.</i>

151
00:16:38,650 --> 00:16:44,901
<i>70,000 M-20 tank destroyers
with 76 mm cannon...</i>

152
00:16:44,926 --> 00:16:46,420
Smith. Syme.

153
00:16:51,036 --> 00:16:53,575
It's encouraging thought
that by 2050

154
00:16:53,783 --> 00:16:57,363
not a single person
could have a conversation like this.

155
00:16:57,643 --> 00:17:02,252
- Except the proles.
- Proletariat don't count. They're animals.

156
00:17:02,277 --> 00:17:05,859
Did you see the hanging?
Missed it myself.

157
00:17:06,193 --> 00:17:08,399
Bloody committees!

158
00:17:08,776 --> 00:17:11,528
<i>... heavy Victory
rocket bombs.</i>

159
00:17:11,758 --> 00:17:19,172
<i>35,000 Black Eagle
500cc motor bicycles. 300,000...</i>

160
00:17:19,807 --> 00:17:21,763
Double plus good this.

161
00:17:21,788 --> 00:17:27,623
Do you know I don't think there is a
single piece of meat in this stew.

162
00:17:27,648 --> 00:17:32,606
Looks like meat, tastes like
meat. It isn't meat at all.

163
00:17:32,631 --> 00:17:35,039
Double plus good.

164
00:17:35,283 --> 00:17:39,280
- Not like it Smith?
- Yes. It's too rich for me.

165
00:17:39,413 --> 00:17:41,452
Do you mind if I?

166
00:17:41,775 --> 00:17:45,339
<i>Brothers and sisters the
battle for production has been won.</i>

167
00:17:46,184 --> 00:17:50,561
<i>Completed returns show that the standard
of living has risen by 20 per cent</i>

168
00:17:50,860 --> 00:17:52,603
<i>over the last year.</i>

169
00:17:52,628 --> 00:17:56,839
<i>All over Oceania, spontaneous
demonstrations of Party workers</i>

170
00:17:57,171 --> 00:18:00,320
<i>Voicing their gratitude and joy.</i>

171
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:04,565
<i>In honour of this massive over fulfilment
of the ninth three year Plan.</i>

172
00:18:04,706 --> 00:18:09,747
<i>It has been announced that the chocolate
ration is to be increased to 25g per week.</i>

173
00:18:18,361 --> 00:18:23,318
If there is hope,
it lies in the proles.

174
00:18:24,114 --> 00:18:29,653
If they were conscious of their strength,
they would have no need to conspire.

175
00:18:29,785 --> 00:18:32,537
History does not matter to them.

176
00:18:42,755 --> 00:18:46,918
It was three years ago,
on a dark evening,

177
00:18:48,351 --> 00:18:50,676
easy to slip the patrols

178
00:18:50,701 --> 00:18:54,117
and I'd gone into the proletarian areas.

179
00:18:57,393 --> 00:19:02,683
There was no one else in the street
and no telescreens.

180
00:19:07,110 --> 00:19:09,149
She said "Two dollars."

181
00:19:11,614 --> 00:19:13,653
So I went with her.

182
00:19:16,504 --> 00:19:21,498
She had a young face, painted very thick.

183
00:19:25,126 --> 00:19:27,581
It was really the paint
that appealed to me,

184
00:19:27,712 --> 00:19:32,338
the whiteness of it like a mask,
and the bright red lips.

185
00:19:52,567 --> 00:19:55,733
There were no preliminaries.

186
00:19:55,862 --> 00:19:59,989
Standing there with the scent
of dead insects and cheap perfume,

187
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:03,199
I went ahead and did it just the same.

188
00:21:04,630 --> 00:21:08,758
Rutherford Unperson, substitute Ogilvy.

189
00:21:09,149 --> 00:21:12,185
Ogilvy biog details as follows.

190
00:21:12,442 --> 00:21:16,903
War hero recently killed Malabar front.

191
00:21:16,929 --> 00:21:21,056
Today awarded posthumous
Order of Conspicuous Merit 2nd class.

192
00:21:29,507 --> 00:21:35,177
<i>I accuse myself of sabotage,
embezzlement of Party funds,</i>

193
00:21:35,202 --> 00:21:40,362
<i>sale of military secrets, of being
in the pay of the government of Eurasia.</i>

194
00:21:40,913 --> 00:21:44,780
<i>Of being a sexual pervert
and a thought criminal.</i>

195
00:21:46,164 --> 00:21:49,783
<i>I exploited my trusted
position at the Ministry of Peace,</i>

196
00:21:49,845 --> 00:21:53,116
<i>to mislead our
allies in Eastasia,</i>

197
00:21:53,141 --> 00:21:59,143
<i>and also to corrupt youth by means
of seditious literature and drugs.</i>

198
00:22:01,450 --> 00:22:08,068
<i>I am guilty on all counts. I stand here
a victim of the influence of Emmanuel...</i>

199
00:22:08,237 --> 00:22:15,318
Under the spreading chestnut
tree I sold you, you sold me.

200
00:22:17,072 --> 00:22:23,442
<i>...and I ask only for you to accept
my love of our leader.</i>

201
00:23:59,056 --> 00:24:01,296
Can I help you?

202
00:24:03,744 --> 00:24:04,744
Hmm.

203
00:24:05,807 --> 00:24:07,847
Anything special?

204
00:24:08,648 --> 00:24:11,222
- I was here before.
- Ah.

205
00:24:11,437 --> 00:24:13,643
- Razor blades.
- Ah-hah.

206
00:24:15,426 --> 00:24:20,170
- You sold me the notebook.
- Yes. Yes.

207
00:24:21,496 --> 00:24:24,366
Please look around.

208
00:24:40,199 --> 00:24:41,397
Ah.

209
00:24:49,403 --> 00:24:51,977
What's this?

210
00:24:52,129 --> 00:24:54,902
Oh it's a beautiful thing.

211
00:24:54,981 --> 00:24:56,551
Over a hundred years old.

212
00:25:00,275 --> 00:25:02,433
Cost you four dollars.

213
00:25:20,150 --> 00:25:23,898
There's another room upstairs
that you might like to see.

214
00:25:24,082 --> 00:25:28,827
Yes it's er, not much in
it. Just a few things.

215
00:26:02,627 --> 00:26:04,869
My woman's dead.

216
00:26:05,089 --> 00:26:08,375
I'm just trying to sell the furniture.

217
00:26:12,894 --> 00:26:17,437
It's a beautiful bed, if you
can get the bugs out of it.

218
00:26:23,035 --> 00:26:26,183
(SOUND OF MISSILE EXPLODING)

219
00:26:28,454 --> 00:26:30,493
Interested in old prints at all?

220
00:26:37,122 --> 00:26:40,407
The frame's fixed to the wall
but I daresay you could unscrew it.

221
00:26:40,666 --> 00:26:43,204
How did this escape?

222
00:26:43,515 --> 00:26:45,887
I know what it is.

223
00:26:46,017 --> 00:26:49,862
It's the museum in the street
outside the Palace of Justice.

224
00:26:49,887 --> 00:26:54,548
Oranges and lemons
say the bells of St Clement's.

225
00:26:54,765 --> 00:26:56,804
What was that?

226
00:26:58,302 --> 00:27:00,341
Something old.

227
00:27:27,966 --> 00:27:30,208
<i>War is peace.</i>

228
00:27:30,421 --> 00:27:32,912
<i>Freedom is slavery.</i>

229
00:27:32,963 --> 00:27:35,418
<i>Ignorance is strength.</i>

230
00:27:38,887 --> 00:27:42,885
<i>A triumph of willpower over the orgasm.</i>

